  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db6\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Two children who were unprotected were taken into police custody",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Midrigiriya police say they have taken into custody two little girls who were staying in a house in the Yudhganawa area of \u200b\u200bMidrigiri.",
        "Police say that one girl is 9 years old and the other girl is 4 years 6 months old.",
        "The mother of these girls left her husband and the two girls about 2 years and 6 months ago and since that day these children have been brought up under their father.",
        "The children's grandmother is also present in this house and she is an elderly woman living alone. The police have been informed that these girls will also carry out all the work of removing her faeces during the afternoon.",
        "Also, after the villagers notified the Child Welfare Authority that the house was very dirty and the children were very unsafe, it was revealed that the children were staying at the place without safety when the police arrived at the house.",
        "The police arranged to provide food to the two fasting children and the station commander and a group of other police officers arranged to provide these girls with clothes, educational equipment, etc."
      ],
